cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper deals with image super-resolution using generative adversarial networks, which is a popular topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of adversarial loss and content loss in the generator loss function suggests that the paper may also fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of 3D convolutions and volumetric information suggests that the paper may also be relevant to neural networks (cs.NE) and multimedia (cs.MM).
